Kotlin is a static typed language used in Android and Server side programming language.
It is 100% interoperable with java.
Kotlin need JVM to run its bytecode.
It is both Functional and Object Oriented programming language.

Kotlin compiler (kotlinc) convertes kotlin source code (.kt) into JVM bytecode (.class) which is executed in JVM.

It has 61 keywords

*Visibility Modifiers-
     4 types -> public , private , internal , protected

    - class members
        public -> access everywhere
        private -> within a class
        protected -> only in subclass
        internal -> within a module

    - top level declaration (outside class)
        public -> access everywhere
        private -> within a file
        protected -> N/A
        internal -> within a module


